HEADWORD: Gallstone
<hw>Gall"stone`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A concretion, or
calculus, formed in the gall bladder or biliary passages. See
<er>Calculus</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, 1.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

